Luke & I ran the remote Boston 5k this morning on Team Imagine to raise money for @danafarber - the hospital that treated my dad who was a marathon runner and passed away of brain cancer. We also ran for the founders of the team, the Mullen’s who used to run with my dad and whose son is now battling cancer at Dana Farber. Thank you so so much to all my friends and community who donated money on our behalf for this team. We were blown away by the generosity and thrilled that together you raised over $1,000 that will go to cancer research. My dad would be so happy that we all spent our days outside together running for a good cause. Thank you thank you ☀️☀️☀️

Yesterday I went to the multi union rally to support the wga strike. It was so inspiring to hear the impassioned speeches and to see tons of people from different unions coming together in enthusiastic support. Chris and I work together and he coaches me on every project I do. When lost he always gives me the note “lean on the script.” All the answers are there in the words where it all begins. Writers create beautiful complex worlds and characters and without them they don’t exist. Proud to be a sag member and to stand in solidarity with the wga. #1u thank you @therealalivingiano for the pic!💛

Happy Father’s Day dad. I miss you always. I went to your favorite place - the water - to find you. You’ve been gone a while but I’m grateful that there you were in the water, in my memories, in me. And I’m grateful that all these years later you’re still getting me out in the sun and reminding me every day is a good one if you make it that. Thanks for making it a good day. 🌊💙

Kenny was as good as it gets. As funny as he was kind. From the first time I met him, he always made me feel so welcome. He radiated joy and warmth and you always left happier after seeing him. The last message I have from Kenny is him telling me he saw I liked a post from a musician and he wanted to tell me that he was an old friend of his and that he was so proud of him. A guy going out of his way to message me to tell me how proud he was of his pal. What a guy. What a loss. Rest in peace Kenny🕊️🦋🩷fundraiser link in my bio for his medical and memorial bills🩷
